-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=1200%2C800&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=1536%2C1024&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=2048%2C1365&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=1240%2C826&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1240w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ipad-Pro-2021-sizes.jpg?resize=150%2C100&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 150w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" loading=\"lazy\" /></figure><p>Dominik Tomaszewski/IDG</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can save a decent amount on most iPads, from time to time we do see really good discounts, especially on the larger capacity models. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>U.S.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Amazon, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BJLXMVMV?tag=macworld05-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">10th-gen iPad (64GB)</a>: $350 ($99 off after coupon, MRSP $449)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Amazon, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09G9FPHY6/?tag=macworld05-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">9th-gen iPad (64GB)</a>: $249 ($80 off, MSRP $329)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Amazon, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09V3JH3XS/?tag=macworld05-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">iPad Air (64GB)</a>: $450 ($149 off, MSRP $599)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Amazon, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09G91LXFP/?tag=macworld05-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">iPad mini (64GB)</a>: $469 ($30 off, MSRP $499)</li>\n\n\n\